## ðŸ’¬ Technical Decisions (Retrospective)

### 1. Why Architecture Matters in Solo Development

I knew that starting a project alone meant that if the initial structure was weak, technical debt would become unmanageable when collaborating with a team later.
Therefore, I focused on building a **'scalable codebase'** by strictly adhering to **Next.js** directory principles and enforcing strong **TypeScript** typing.

### 2. Experience with Monetization (Paddle)

This project provided experience beyond simple feature development; I learned how to build a **'profitable service'**. Integrating the **Paddle** payment module gave me a deep understanding of the entire payment flow, including managing subscription lifecycles and handling webhooks.
